  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Activity 1.1. Conduct a regional workshop involving pilot countries, key national and regional stakeholders\r\n\r\nActivity 1.2. Conduct inception workshop in each pilot country\r\n\r\nActivity 1.3. Review current policies and practices on tenure and identify policy gaps in each pilot country\r\n\r\nActivity 1.4. Conduct a regional workshop to share lessons learned\r\n\r\nActivity 2.1. Develop action plan to strengthen forest tenure policies and practices in pilot countries building on existing plan in each country\r\n\r\nActivity 2.2. Conduct national multi-stakeholder meetings in each pilot countries to share, review and finalize the action plan\r\n\r\nActivity 3.1. Conduct institutional capacity assessment for tenure in pilot countries\r\n\r\nActivity 3.2. Produce a Capacity Development action plan for medium term (3-5 years) and short term (1-2 years)\r\n\r\nActivity 4.1. Conduct forest tenure training involving government and non-government organizations in each country using ToT approach\r\n\r\nActivity 4.2. Conduct awareness raising on forest tenure in each country using various means such as media, posters, short video, etc.\r\n\r\nActivity 4.3. Conduct an exposure visit for governments of the pilot countries to learn about forest tenure"
    },
    "ne": null
  },
